headline: Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan Sells Large Block of This Tech Stock
summary: Intel  CEO Lip-Bu Tan recently sold a large block of shares of a technology company that he serves as a director.  On June 6, Tan sold 75,000 shares of  Credo Technology Group Holding  a provider of high-speed connectivity solutions, for $5.6 million, an average price of $75.20 each.

headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock to Keep an Eye On and 2 to Steer Clear Of
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is home to the biggest and most well-known companies in the market, making it a go-to index for investors seeking stability. But not all large-cap stocks are created equal - some are struggling with slowing growth, declining margins, or increased competition.

headline: Q1 Earnings Outperformers: Allegro MicroSystems (NASDAQ:ALGM) And The Rest Of The Processors and Graphics Chips Stocks
summary: Quarterly earnings results are a good time to check in on a company’s progress, especially compared to its peers in the same sector. Today we are looking at Allegro MicroSystems (NASDAQ:ALGM) and the best and worst performers in the processors and graphics chips industry.
